WEBVTT

01:19.862 --> 01:21.457
[PANTING]

01:40.341 --> 01:41.918
[MOANS]

01:50.740 --> 01:52.830
Oh, baby.

01:54.630 --> 01:56.229
Tommy.

01:56.329 --> 01:57.930
Tommy.

01:59.668 --> 02:01.226
[MOANING]

02:07.779 --> 02:10.364
Mmm. That was great, baby.

02:16.929 --> 02:18.478
[GROANS]

02:37.246 --> 02:38.746
Jody.

02:39.546 --> 02:42.231
- Hi, Reg.
- How's it goin'?

02:44.346 --> 02:46.441
Tommy's gone.

02:48.046 --> 02:51.346
It's, uh... it's a hell of a way
to end a trio.

02:51.446 --> 02:54.945
It's hard to believe... he killed himself.

02:55.045 --> 02:59.446
Yeah, I, uh... I'm gonna go visit somebody.
I'll catch ya inside.

02:59.546 --> 03:01.131
Yeah.

03:35.480 --> 03:37.098
[GROWLING]

03:41.579 --> 03:42.747
[GROWLING]

04:22.199 --> 04:23.730
[MOTOR RUNNING]

04:49.396 --> 04:50.940
[ENGINE DIES]

05:01.247 --> 05:03.353
[ENGINE REVS, DIES]

05:04.979 --> 05:06.429
[GROWLING]

05:14.396 --> 05:15.992
[GROWLING]

05:27.346 --> 05:28.935
[GROWLING]

05:44.729 --> 05:46.279
[GROWLING]

06:07.329 --> 06:08.914
[GROWLING]

06:32.246 --> 06:35.463
The funeral is about to begin... sir.

06:37.963 --> 06:39.462
Okay.

06:40.384 --> 06:41.963
Sir.

06:43.565 --> 06:45.130
[ORGAN]

06:59.575 --> 07:02.512
REGGIE: It was a good idea not to let
your little brother come to the funeral

07:02.612 --> 07:04.412
and see Tommy like this.

07:04.512 --> 07:08.413
JODY: Yeah, after Mom and Dad's funeral,
he had nightmares for weeks.

08:13.579 --> 08:17.662
And forgive us our debts
as we forgive our debtors.

08:17.762 --> 08:22.496
Lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.

08:25.863 --> 08:27.572
Hey, I don't like this place.

08:27.672 --> 08:30.746
REGGIE: Well, say goodbye to Tommy.

08:31.395 --> 08:33.768
JODY: Let's just get the hell out of here.

10:12.479 --> 10:15.579
- Hi, Michael.
- Hi. Uh... is your grandmother home?

10:15.679 --> 10:17.763
Sure. Come in.

10:25.746 --> 10:29.589
Grandmother. Michael has returned
and wishes to speak with you.

10:38.762 --> 10:42.396
Grandmother is pleased you've come
and wants to know what's bothering you.

10:43.096 --> 10:45.382
Uh, tell her that I, um...

10:45.482 --> 10:46.864
She can hear you.

10:47.629 --> 10:49.429
Oh, yeah.

10:49.929 --> 10:52.828
Uh, it's Jody again.

10:52.928 --> 10:54.650
I found out that he's leaving.

11:37.886 --> 11:39.577
[WHISTLING]

11:39.677 --> 11:42.047
I think it's one of these headers in here.

11:46.162 --> 11:47.747
[CAR APPROACHING]

11:55.946 --> 11:58.429
Hey, Toby! Hey.

11:59.029 --> 12:02.107
- So what brings you back?
- Tommy.

12:02.207 --> 12:04.662
Yeah, yeah.

12:04.762 --> 12:08.328
Well, I just don't get off on funerals, man.
They give me the creeps.

12:08.678 --> 12:11.929
I just wanted to tell you I heard
about your folks. I'm really sorry.

12:12.029 --> 12:14.429
Yeah, thank you, man. That's, uh...

12:14.529 --> 12:17.562
In two years I guess you can
just about get over anything.

12:18.062 --> 12:21.412
- So I hear you've been out on the road.
- Yeah.

12:21.612 --> 12:23.278
How come you're hanging around this dump?

12:23.378 --> 12:25.545
Well, I'm taking care
of the kid, you know.

12:25.645 --> 12:30.294
Shit, I think after, uh, all that action,
this town would drive you nuts.

12:30.394 --> 12:33.812
You're damn right. Hell, the kid's 13 now.

12:33.912 --> 12:36.963
Yeah, I'm thinking of sending him
off to live with his aunt.

12:37.063 --> 12:39.546
<i>But I'll tell you,
he sure ain't gonna like it.</i>

12:39.646 --> 12:44.812
<i>I mean, as it is, he follows me everywhere.
It's like he knows I'm gonna leave.</i>

12:44.912 --> 12:47.412
<i>He's a tough little kid. I love him.</i>

12:47.512 --> 12:49.597
<i>I'm gonna miss him.</i>

12:57.946 --> 13:00.012
Grandmother has told you
before not to worry.

13:00.112 --> 13:02.712
If he does leave, he'll take you with him.

13:02.812 --> 13:05.980
- God, I hope she's right.
- She always is.

13:08.862 --> 13:11.162
Uh, there's something else.

13:11.862 --> 13:14.133
I'm really scared
about something that I did.

13:14.233 --> 13:18.595
I was messing around up at Morningside
Cemetery, and I saw something.

13:18.695 --> 13:20.780
Something really scary.

13:49.746 --> 13:51.297
[ENGINE SPUTTERS]

14:14.712 --> 14:17.896
Michael, grandmother
wants to play a little game.

14:19.011 --> 14:21.278
Wow! How'd you do that?

14:21.378 --> 14:23.079
Put your hand in the box.

14:24.495 --> 14:28.163
- Well, what's in it?
- Just put your hand in the black box.

14:30.012 --> 14:32.462
Okay, but what's in it?

14:32.762 --> 14:34.345
[CLANGING]

14:34.945 --> 14:36.745
Hey, this thing really hurts!

14:36.845 --> 14:39.045
Don't fear, Michael.

14:39.645 --> 14:42.862
- I can't get my hand out.
- Don't fear.

14:43.412 --> 14:46.646
- Give me back my hand!
- Don't fear!

14:54.145 --> 14:56.558
It was simply reflection.
Fear is the killer.

14:56.658 --> 14:59.204
That's what grandmother
wants you to learn.

14:59.978 --> 15:02.246
Boy, that really hurt.

15:04.712 --> 15:06.813
It was all in your mind.

15:10.312 --> 15:12.145
Oh, yeah.

15:21.945 --> 15:24.112
Come and visit us again soon.

15:24.212 --> 15:25.730
Yeah.

15:30.729 --> 15:32.313
[LAUGHS]

16:01.696 --> 16:03.250
[HUMMING]

16:17.078 --> 16:18.778
- Hiya, Reg.
- Writing a new tune?

16:18.878 --> 16:20.962
Yeah, working on it.

16:27.579 --> 16:31.063
<i># I'm just a-sittin' here at midnight #</i>

16:34.378 --> 16:37.862
<i># And I'll be sitting here 'til noon #</i>

16:41.278 --> 16:44.961
<i># You see, my lady left me lonely #</i>

16:45.479 --> 16:47.480
<i># Yes, she did #</i>

16:48.679 --> 16:51.979
<i># My baby left me blue #</i>

16:53.078 --> 16:54.663
[BOTH GRUNT]

17:15.429 --> 17:16.929
[LAUGHING]

17:17.928 --> 17:20.928
All right. We're hot as love, you know.

17:21.228 --> 17:22.765
[TUNING FORK TONE]

17:27.428 --> 17:28.996
[TONE STOPS]

17:30.095 --> 17:31.398
[LOUD TONE]

17:43.845 --> 17:45.358
[TONE GROWS LOUDER]

17:47.412 --> 17:48.913
[SCREAMS]

18:58.195 --> 19:00.695
Well, let's see.

19:01.495 --> 19:04.480
This is, uh... just right up the street.

19:07.895 --> 19:09.281
[DOG BARKING]

20:05.595 --> 20:07.596
This is, uh...

20:07.995 --> 20:11.796
- kinda spooky, isn't it?
- No, it's exciting.

20:12.995 --> 20:14.995
So, uh...

20:15.395 --> 20:18.196
what's the only thing to do in this town?

20:19.395 --> 20:21.984
Well, it's something...

20:42.011 --> 20:43.113
[MOANS]

21:02.295 --> 21:03.779
Wow.

21:04.445 --> 21:06.029
Wow.

21:23.794 --> 21:25.381
[GROWLING]

21:32.661 --> 21:34.259
[FOOTSTEPS]

21:41.878 --> 21:43.380
[GROWLING]

22:05.928 --> 22:07.513
[GROWLING]

22:16.278 --> 22:18.062
[YELLING]

22:20.178 --> 22:22.429
- What the heck?
- [YELLING]

22:23.028 --> 22:25.494
Wait here. It's my little brother.

22:25.594 --> 22:28.012
I think he's got some kind of a problem.

22:32.544 --> 22:34.087
[YELLING]

22:49.378 --> 22:50.962
Mike!

22:53.728 --> 22:55.701
What's wrong with you, man?

22:55.801 --> 22:58.894
There's something up there.
I know it. I saw it!

22:58.994 --> 23:00.244
What?

23:00.344 --> 23:02.661
Okay, look, I was following you guys.

23:02.761 --> 23:05.845
I didn't mean any harm,
but it's out there and it's gonna get me!

23:06.944 --> 23:09.861
- What's out there?
- I don't know.

23:09.961 --> 23:12.798
It was little and brown
and low to the ground.

23:13.577 --> 23:15.744
It was probably just a gopher in heat.

23:15.844 --> 23:18.112
It wasn't any gopher!

23:18.761 --> 23:20.394
Where's that girl, anyway?

23:20.494 --> 23:23.032
Well, she's waiting back there
for me, you idiot.

23:23.132 --> 23:24.645
[GROWLING]

23:24.745 --> 23:26.745
Did you hear that?

23:27.145 --> 23:29.362
Eh, it's only the wind.

23:30.760 --> 23:32.944
You better go get her before it gets her.

23:33.044 --> 23:36.703
You got some kind of an overactive
imagination or something, man?

23:37.244 --> 23:40.112
Look, tell you what.

23:41.111 --> 23:44.978
You go on home.
I'll talk to you when I get back.

23:45.427 --> 23:49.310
- You sure you're gonna be okay?
- Ah, get out of here.

25:20.928 --> 25:22.515
[GROWLING]

25:28.128 --> 25:29.714
[SCREAMING]

27:08.627 --> 27:10.213
[SNIFFS]

27:30.827 --> 27:34.262
Did that chick that I left with
last night ever come back in here?

27:34.362 --> 27:37.277
What happened? You get a hold
of something you couldn't handle?

27:37.377 --> 27:40.978
Nah, she just ditched out on me, I guess.

27:41.777 --> 27:43.789
We were...

27:44.300 --> 27:46.785
messing around out there at Morningside.

27:46.885 --> 27:49.978
- The funeral parlor?
- Yeah. Cemetery.

27:50.078 --> 27:51.629
[LAUGHS]

28:14.377 --> 28:15.929
[GROWLING]

28:20.477 --> 28:23.361
Jody? Is that you?

28:29.678 --> 28:31.263
[GROWLING]

28:53.027 --> 28:54.545
[RATTLING]

29:05.794 --> 29:07.362
[SCREECH]

29:19.444 --> 29:21.013
[GROANING]

29:25.127 --> 29:26.575
[SCREAMS]

29:27.194 --> 29:28.978
You hit my fucking foot, man.

29:29.177 --> 29:31.929
Oh, damn. I know you're not gonna
believe this, but these things were here.

29:32.029 --> 29:34.093
Right in the garage
and they were gonna get me.

29:34.193 --> 29:35.964
Ah, gimme a break, will ya?

29:36.064 --> 29:39.728
They were jumping on the car
and making these weird sounds.

29:39.828 --> 29:42.477
Sure it wasn't that retarded kid,
Timmy, up the street?

29:42.577 --> 29:45.881
No, it was the same thing
that chased me last night.

29:46.011 --> 29:48.278
Well, what are we gonna do?

29:49.994 --> 29:51.879
You're crazy, man.

31:08.260 --> 31:09.797
[GATE RATTLING]

34:00.977 --> 34:02.479
[DOOR BANGS]

36:12.044 --> 36:13.630
[BANGING NOISE]

36:19.545 --> 36:21.129
[BANGING NOISE]

36:25.010 --> 36:27.028
[BANGING, RATTLING]

36:34.110 --> 36:35.745
[WHIRRING NOISE]

36:39.877 --> 36:41.429
[PANTING]

36:45.377 --> 36:46.945
[GAGGING]

36:48.943 --> 36:50.512
[WHIRRING]

36:54.927 --> 36:56.495
[SCREAMING]

36:58.511 --> 37:00.564
[WHIRRING CONTINUES]

37:04.443 --> 37:05.980
[SCREAMING]

37:50.110 --> 37:51.912
Um...

37:53.511 --> 37:55.645
Oh, shit.

38:15.877 --> 38:17.896
[LOUD RUSTLING NOISE]

38:29.094 --> 38:30.681
[TAPPING]

38:37.444 --> 38:38.648
[SCREAMING]

38:47.760 --> 38:49.261
[SCREAMING STOPS]

38:50.260 --> 38:51.844
[POUNDING]

38:58.177 --> 38:59.727
[FOOTSTEPS]

38:59.827 --> 39:01.363
[GASPS]

39:05.477 --> 39:07.046
[GROWLING]

39:09.344 --> 39:10.902
[GRUNTING]

39:39.377 --> 39:40.963
[TOILET FLUSHES]

40:20.476 --> 40:22.393
I've gotta talk to you.

40:22.493 --> 40:24.777
And it's in that box?

40:25.027 --> 40:26.611
Yep.

40:47.977 --> 40:50.410
Okay. I believe you.

40:51.110 --> 40:52.661
Jesus!

40:55.161 --> 40:57.245
What's goin' on up there?

40:57.345 --> 40:59.728
Well, there's something I didn't tell ya.

41:00.427 --> 41:04.327
I was spyin' on Tommy's funeral
from the Groves with your binoculars.

41:04.427 --> 41:06.650
And after everybody had left,

41:06.750 --> 41:10.363
that Tall Man picked up
Tommy's coffin all by himself

41:10.463 --> 41:12.127
and put it in the hearse and drove off.

41:12.227 --> 41:15.427
You're crazy!
I helped carry that sucker myself.

41:15.527 --> 41:17.728
It must've weighed over 500 pounds.

41:19.027 --> 41:20.612
[SIGHS]

41:22.927 --> 41:25.128
I can't figure this thing out.

41:26.327 --> 41:29.928
But I do know one thing.
Something weird is going on up there.

41:31.027 --> 41:33.427
We're goin' for the sheriff.
Go get your evidence.

41:33.527 --> 41:35.461
All right!

41:42.960 --> 41:44.594
That's funny.

41:55.877 --> 41:57.262
[SCREECHING]

41:59.844 --> 42:01.369
[CLICKING NOISE]

42:09.844 --> 42:11.396
[BUZZING NOISE]

42:16.443 --> 42:19.731
Jody! Jody!

42:25.260 --> 42:27.344
JODY: What the...

42:35.326 --> 42:37.415
The garbage disposal.

42:38.261 --> 42:39.914
- Come on.
- [BUZZING]

42:51.677 --> 42:54.176
Ready? Go!

42:54.276 --> 42:56.362
[DISPOSAL MOTOR WHIRRING]

43:00.977 --> 43:02.560
[WHIRRING STOPS]

43:08.660 --> 43:10.661
Would you look at that?

43:11.061 --> 43:12.576
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

43:19.211 --> 43:21.011
Hey, guys.

43:22.259 --> 43:24.911
I thought I'd come over
and see what was goin' on

43:25.011 --> 43:26.727
before the kids got out of summer school.

43:26.827 --> 43:29.110
Mike, you wanna ride along with me today?

43:29.210 --> 43:33.757
It's pretty warm outside and the ice cream's
gonna be flying fast and furious.

43:33.977 --> 43:37.593
Remember how good you were
at crowd control last time?

43:37.693 --> 43:38.960
Hey, what's goin' on here?

43:39.060 --> 43:41.273
- [LOUD BUZZING]
- [SCREAMS]

43:53.577 --> 43:55.095
[DISPOSAL WHIRRING]

44:02.543 --> 44:04.129
[WHIRRING STOPS]

44:07.927 --> 44:10.510
What the hell is goin' on?

44:11.509 --> 44:14.076
Here, you keep that.

44:14.176 --> 44:18.078
Now remember, you don't aim a gun
at a man unless you intend to shoot him.

44:18.777 --> 44:22.577
And you don't shoot a man
unless you intend to kill him.

44:23.276 --> 44:25.477
No warning shots.

44:25.577 --> 44:27.176
- Hey, you listening to me?
- Yeah.

44:27.276 --> 44:30.277
No warning shots.
Warning shots are bullshit.

44:30.577 --> 44:33.577
You shoot to kill
or you don't shoot at all.

44:33.977 --> 44:38.078
Now you'll be safe here.
Lock all the doors and windows.

44:38.877 --> 44:42.777
- And don't follow me.
- You sure you're gonna be okay with that?

44:42.877 --> 44:46.677
I'm just gonna go up there and take
a look around. Nobody's gonna see me.

44:47.276 --> 44:51.995
But, heck, a Colt Army issue
will put a man down and keep him there.

44:56.343 --> 44:59.844
Remember that broken basement
window around by the side.

45:00.443 --> 45:02.528
And be careful.

47:09.510 --> 47:11.596
- [GROWLING]
- [GRUNTS]

47:19.026 --> 47:21.621
- [GRUNTING, GROANING]
- [GROWLING]

47:22.677 --> 47:24.261
[BITING]

47:31.243 --> 47:32.746
[GUNSHOT]

47:44.643 --> 47:46.177
[PANTING]

47:51.460 --> 47:53.094
[ENGINE REVVING]

48:14.993 --> 48:16.495
[GUNSHOT]

48:41.426 --> 48:42.928
[PANTING]

48:47.943 --> 48:50.328
All right, who's in there?

48:55.343 --> 48:56.928
Mike?

49:02.543 --> 49:05.211
Damn door latch. Get in.

49:11.660 --> 49:14.043
Oh, here it comes!

49:14.243 --> 49:16.577
There's nobody drivin' that mother!

49:21.343 --> 49:23.578
The pump's in the backseat.

49:26.059 --> 49:29.477
Okay. Slow down,
and let him ride right up on our ass.

49:39.743 --> 49:42.077
There was nobody...
there was nobody driving!

49:44.676 --> 49:46.993
I'm gonna get that bastard.

49:55.226 --> 49:57.361
Oh, Jesus.

50:03.310 --> 50:06.843
All right, speed up.
I want to put a few in the engine.

50:06.943 --> 50:08.529
Okay.

50:13.993 --> 50:16.177
Holy shit!

50:21.760 --> 50:23.345
[WHOOPING]

51:05.343 --> 51:07.742
JODY: It's one of those dwarves.

51:07.842 --> 51:09.638
It went right through it.

51:25.859 --> 51:27.445
Tommy!

51:30.092 --> 51:31.611
Reggie.

51:35.026 --> 51:36.911
We got one of 'em.

51:40.326 --> 51:43.111
Uh, on Colton in the Groves.

51:45.326 --> 51:48.011
All right. Uh, Reg?

51:50.026 --> 51:52.111
Bring your truck.

51:55.243 --> 51:59.257
Holy Jesus!
You didn't tell me the dwarf was Tommy.

51:59.876 --> 52:03.377
Hell, we buried him on Monday,
and look what they did to him.

52:03.876 --> 52:07.760
He's only three feet long!
He must still weigh 200 pounds.

52:09.276 --> 52:11.876
What's all this yellow shit
coming out of his head?

52:11.976 --> 52:14.127
Careful. Get him in there.

52:16.043 --> 52:18.828
- Better padlock it.
- Yeah.

52:22.643 --> 52:26.227
This guy's not gonna leak
all over my ice cream, is he?

52:28.842 --> 52:30.943
We'll see you back at the house.

52:31.043 --> 52:32.595
Right.

53:08.976 --> 53:11.244
You boys back yet?

53:12.859 --> 53:17.159
Jesus Christ, Myrtle.
You almost gave me a coronary.

53:17.409 --> 53:19.994
But I just can't figure out why.

53:22.209 --> 53:26.909
Why they're taking these bodies
and crushing them down to half size.

53:27.209 --> 53:28.610
Crushing 'em.

53:28.909 --> 53:30.926
What about Mom and Dad?

53:31.825 --> 53:33.910
They're up there too.

53:42.959 --> 53:45.793
Hey, just forget about that.

53:47.376 --> 53:48.877
Okay.

53:49.676 --> 53:52.076
I see it. I see it all now.

53:52.576 --> 53:56.477
What we gotta do is we gotta
snag that tall dude,

53:56.577 --> 53:58.376
and stomp the shit out of him.

53:58.476 --> 54:01.477
And we'll find out what the hell
is going on up there.

54:02.276 --> 54:06.642
Yeah. We'll lay that sucker out flat and
drive a stake through his goddamn heart!

54:07.092 --> 54:09.927
You gotta be shittin' me, man.
That mother's strong.

54:12.559 --> 54:16.377
Hey, hold on. First thing is,
I want Mike out of here.

54:17.176 --> 54:20.377
JODY: Reg, you take him
over to Sally's, the antique store.

54:20.477 --> 54:22.776
He'll be safe there. Then hustle on back.

54:22.876 --> 54:25.812
And, Mike, no arguments.

54:34.510 --> 54:37.459
SALLY:
Jody sure sounded strange on the phone.

54:37.559 --> 54:39.260
I hope he's feeling okay.

54:39.360 --> 54:41.844
Sally, did you see these new settings?

54:44.159 --> 54:46.244
Oh, these are nice.

54:48.326 --> 54:50.609
You know, I think I'm gonna lock up.

54:50.709 --> 54:52.295
[CLOCK TICKING]

54:55.460 --> 54:59.559
SALLY: Michael, when you get sleepy,
I've got a bed made up for you in back.

54:59.659 --> 55:01.213
[TICKING CONTINUES]

56:27.909 --> 56:29.609
- You have to take me home.
- But why?

56:29.709 --> 56:32.210
No questions. You must take me home.

56:32.310 --> 56:33.879
[PLAYING "THREE BLIND MICE"]

56:38.518 --> 56:40.081
[THUMPING NOISE]

56:41.093 --> 56:42.681
[GROWLING]

57:01.659 --> 57:03.178
[RUSTLING NOISE]

57:05.893 --> 57:07.463
[HOWLING]

57:18.959 --> 57:20.508
[GROWLING]

57:39.693 --> 57:42.078
Oh, my God. Pull over.

57:47.892 --> 57:51.760
MICHAEL: Stay in the car
and don't get out. I'll be right back.

57:53.276 --> 57:55.861
